<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="17">Material examined. SIO 72-189, male, 50 mm SL, 55 mm TL, Sta. MV72-II-32, 15° 39.2 S, 76° 13.6' W, Peru (Nazca Ridge), 10-11 May 1972, 8 m otter trawl, ca. 3475 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="17">
This specimen is small and somewhat damaged, but fits the species description well in all particulars. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1D67D1B5-B4DF-4C7D-8412-70CC01A828BE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Liparidae" genus="Careproctus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Careproctus longifilis Garman 1892:9" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longifilis">Careproctus longifilis</taxonomicName>
was redescribed by Stein (1978) who described its range as from Panama to Oregon, predicting that “more specimens would be reported from deep water throughout the eastern Pacific Ocean.” This specimen extends the range considerably further south to Peru. The species seems to have an unusually broad range for a snailfish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
